Trains have been suspended between Picton and Moss Vale in both directions due to heavy rainfall affecting rail infrastructure. Bus companies are being contacted to operate a replacement service until train services can resume. Limited buses will start arriving at around 19:45 hrs. 

Please allow plenty of additional travel time, check station information screens and listen for announcements for updates. We recommend delaying your journey, catch local bu routes or making alternative arrangements where possible. 

We are closely monitoring the situation and updates will be provided as information becomes available.

Please allow additional travel time, due to external power supply issues affecting rail infrastructure between Warrimoo and Faulconbridge. 

There may be a larger-than-usual gap between services at some stations. Services are moving through the affected area, although the will be delayed in both directions. Please check information screens and listen to announcements for the latest service information.
With wet weather predicted over the next few days, please avoid rushing and take extra care while getting on and off the train.

Sydney Super Fight -  Bankwest Stadium, Parramatta
17:30 to 22:30
- The closest station to Bankwest Stadium is Parramatta. The stadium is approximately 15 minutes walk from the station exiting via Darcy St then continuing on Church St, the Riverside Walk (non-accessible route) or through Prince Alfred Square to the stadium on O'Connell St.

For more information visit https://transportnsw.info/events/2020/12/sydney-super-fight

There are changes happening at Central Station during Sydney Metro construction works. Access to certain areas of the station and platforms may be limited, which means using different stairs, escalators and lifts. 

Please follow the signs and staff directions. If you need assistance, see station staff. 

For detailed information please visit https://transportnsw.info/alerts/details#/6049959

There are changes at Sydenham station during Sydney Metro construction.

T3 Bankstown Line services to the City are available from platform 3 and to Lidcombe and Liverpool from platform 4.

A new Metro concourse is also being constructed at the Northern end of the station. While the concourse is being installed, please board and alight from the first 5 carriages of the train on platforms 4 & 6 and the last 6 carriages of the train on platform 5.

If you need help, please see staff at the station. For more information on these upgrades, please see sydneymetro.info

Due to construction works happening on a nearby building, the York Lane entry/exit to Wynyard Station will be closed from 9pm until 5am on Sunday 13, Monday 14 & Tuesday 15 December. Access to/from the station will still be available via the Clarence St & York St entry/exits. If you need assistance, see station staff.
